    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-16T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-16T08:00:00-05:00" n="644"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/1707: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-16T16:00:00+03:00"
                            >November 16, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 17—1:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1964. Personal for the Under Secretary. Reference Embassy’s 1677, October
                        22;<note n="46" xml:id="d644fn46">Not printed.</note> 1880, November 9, and
                    1934, November 13. I hope you will review the above telegrams referring to the
                    question of aid to the Soviet Union during reconstruction, together with
                    Nelson’s discussions.</p>
                <p>I am not sure I have made it clear that this question of reconstruction is
                    considered by the Soviet Government as, next to the war, the most important
                    political as well as economic problem that confronts <pb facs="0801" n="789"
                        xml:id="pg_789"/> them. Our participation in reconstruction is an important
                    and integral part of our diplomatic dealings with them and it is therefore in my
                    judgment essential that the negotiations be handled under the direction of those
                    dealing with our overall relations with the Soviet Union and not be a new
                    independent agency or group. I would appreciate your giving me the benefit of
                    any preliminary ideas that are being developed on this subject.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
